solution: The side length of square $A_1$ is $\sqrt{25}=5$ cm, and the side length of square $A_2$ is $\sqrt{49}=7$ cm.  Therefore, rectangle $A_3$ is 5 cm by 7 cm and has area $(5\text{ cm})(7\text{ cm})=\boxed{35}$ square centimeters.
model_solution:
The length of the side of square $A_1$ is $\sqrt{25\text{ cm}^2}=5$ centimeters.
The length of the side of square $A_2$ is $\sqrt{49\text{ cm}^2}=7$ centimeters.
Since the length of the side of $A_2$ is 7 centimeters, the width of $A_3$ is 7 centimeters. Since the length of the side of $A_1$ is 5 centimeters, the length of $A_3$ is 5 centimeters.
The area of $A_3$ is $7\text{ cm}\cdot5\text{ cm}=35\text{ cm}^2$.
